  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "Interest in the blend of differential equations, deep learning and dynamical systems has been reignited by recent works [[1](https://arxiv.org/abs/1806.07366),[2](https://arxiv.org/abs/2001.04385), [3](https://arxiv.org/abs/2002.08071), [4](https://arxiv.org/abs/1909.01377)]. Modern deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch, coupled with further improvements in computational resources have allowed the continuous version of neural networks, with proposals dating back to the 80s [[5](https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/6814892)], to finally come to life and provide a novel perspective on classical machine learning problems.",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
